# Layout safety

## Root shell
`RootShell`: `extendBody: false`. Bottom nav uses its own `SafeArea`. Do not enable root `extendBody: true` without explicit approval.

## Full-bleed screens (Home, Events, …)
Often: `extendBodyBehindAppBar: true`, manual top inset via `MediaQuery.paddingOf(context).top + …`.

When editing layout on these screens, follow the **same file’s** existing pattern. Do not wrap the whole tab in `SafeArea` if it shrinks the hero.

## Sheets & keyboard
`showModalBottomSheet` + `isScrollControlled: true`: account for `MediaQuery.viewInsetsOf(context).bottom` (see `event_signup_sheet.dart`).

## IndexedStack
All five tabs stay mounted. After `async`, check `mounted` in post-frame callbacks.

## After layout changes, verify
- Bottom nav does not cover primary CTA.
- Status bar readable on dark heroes.
- If shell or tab bar changed: `flutter test test/navigation_test.dart`.
